Kevin,

Yep, that can be a pain.  I&#39;ve only gotten bit by it once every couple
weeks, which is about half as often as I appreciate the fact that
quick-fix on

assertThat(myNewMethod(), is(&quot;abc&quot;));

creates

String myNewMethod() {
}

so for me, hamcrest does optimize for the common case.

That said, you could pretty easily write your own matcher, if this
came up a lot.  I tried once to figure out how to automatically get
the stricter typing when I wanted it, and the looser when I didn&#39;t,
but there&#39;s always trade-offs to be made.  If you do end up writing
your own, (1) consider submitting it to hamcrest, and (2) let me know
what the name is (I can&#39;t think of a good one).

On the meta-question, the developers hang around
hamcrest-dev@... (which I&#39;ve CC&#39;ed), so they can pipe in
with further ideas.  There&#39;s also hamcrest-java@..., but
I don&#39;t know if anyone listens there.  Hamcrest will soon be shipping
along with JUnit, so I figure ours won&#39;t be the last hamcrest
question.  Thanks,

   David Saff

